                            <comment id="13983043" author="srowen" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2014 15:32:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Some small suggestions:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If you want to make a File representing a file in a subdirectory represented by a File, you can just...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;File dir = ...;&lt;br/&gt;
File file = new File(dir, ...);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Clean and no platform-dependence.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;For detecting Windows, try SystemUtils, from Commons Lang, which is already a dependency.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/apidocs/org/apache/commons/lang3/SystemUtils.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/apidocs/org/apache/commons/lang3/SystemUtils.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SystemUtils.IS_OS_WINDOWS&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Is that change to add -Djava.library.path going to be OK on non-Windows systems? it has a backslash.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13983047" author="ssvinarchukhorton" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2014 15:40:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, this mahout build with this patch on Linux and Windows.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll update path to use SystemUtils.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13983064" author="ssvinarchukhorton" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2014 15:56:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I attached updated patch with using SystemUtils.IS_OS_WINDOWS&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13983073" author="srowen" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2014 16:05:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I also meant that instead of&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
File tmpFile = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.getProperty(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
ModelSerializer.writeBinary(tmpFile.getAbsoluteFile().toString()+&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.getProperty(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;file.separator&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)+&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;news-group.model&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;you can do &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
ModelSerializer.writeBinary(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File(SystemUtils.getJavaIoTmpDir(), &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;news-group.model&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).toString(),
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but this is pretty trivial.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the spark module, does it really need its own separate Hadoop dependencies and different Hadoop 2 profile? I&apos;m not questioning it, just curious. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a different question, but does CDH really belong here as a separate profile, instead of just having a Hadoop 2 profile &amp;#8211; can they be &apos;merged&apos;? It shouldn&apos;t be a special case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13983076" author="ssc" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2014 16:07:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m testing the patch and fixing the trivial file creation issue thereby.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13983084" author="ssvinarchukhorton" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2014 16:12:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, we can merged hadoop2 and CDH profile in spark&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
